# Supabase — powers shared, multi-user crowd hazard reports.
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in from your project's API settings
# (Project Settings → API). Both are safe to expose in a client bundle:
# the anon key is a public key gated by row-level security (see
# supabase/schema.sql). Leave these unset to run reports in
# localStorage-only mode (no backend, submissions stay in your browser).
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
